  "prompt": "Is it normal to be extremely motivated for few months and extremely depressed for few months?",
  "response": "Experiencing fluctuations in mood and motivation can be a normal part of life, but the pattern you described may suggest something more significant. It could be related to various factors, including lifestyle, stress, personal circumstances, or underlying mental health conditions. \n\nIn some cases, such cyclical changes might be indicative of mood disorders such as Bipolar Disorder or Seasonal Affective Disorder (SAD). Bipolar Disorder typically involves periods of intense highs (mania or hypomania) and lows (depression). SAD typically occurs in a cyclical pattern with depressive episodes during specific seasons.\n\nIt is essential to monitor these changes and consider seeking advice from a healthcare professional, such as a therapist or psychiatrist. They can help to evaluate your symptoms, provide a diagnosis if necessary, and offer appropriate treatment options. It is also helpful to practice self-care, maintain a balanced lifestyle, seek social support, and manage stress effectively to mitigate extreme moods.\n\nRemember, seeking professional help is crucial if your mood fluctuations significantly impair your daily functioning or quality of life.",
